verbose_text: LncRNA steroid receptor RNA activator (SRA) was originally identified as an LncRNA that coordinates the functions of various transcription factors and enhances steroid nuclear receptor dependent gene expression, such as estrogen receptor alpha (ERalpha) and androgen receptor (AR) [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
evidence: enhances steroid nuclear receptor-dependent gene expression, such as estrogen receptor alpha (ERalpha) and androgen receptor
